                <note type="abstract">On ibn Bal‘am’s commentary on the Minor Prophets. In his footnotes to the edited text of Ibn Balʿam’s commentary Poznański sporadically cites the anonymous reworking of Yefet b. Eli’s Judaeo-Arabic translation of the Latter Prophets in Ms. Hunt. 206 of the Bodleian Library (per those portions edited by Heisz {https://www.zotero.org/groups/biblia_arabica/items/itemKey/JR39UDLB}, Klein <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/TP5YI7J7">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/TP5YI7J7</ref>, Friedmann <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/IGJ5MT8M">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/IGJ5MT8M</ref>, and Schröter <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/2EEXHZ9V">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/2EEXHZ9V</ref>
                    <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/DVM2SEFS">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/DVM2SEFS</ref>). On the later identification of this Ms. with Yefet’s work see, inter alios, P. Birnbaum’s 1942 edition of Yefet on Hosea <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/34RLRYC5">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/34RLRYC5</ref> and E. Schlossberg’s 2000 Pe‘amim article <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/NY3EPQ72">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/NY3EPQ72</ref>.</note>
